---
target: core/graph
version: 1
validations:
  - name: graph-module-exists
    type: folder_check
    path: src/graph

  - name: graph-structure-defined
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify the graph module defines:
      1. A DAG type with nodes (indexed by name) and roots (nodes with no dependencies)
      2. A Node type with Name, Target, Dependencies, and Dependents
      3. Functions: NewDAG, AddTarget, Resolve, DetectCycles, TopologicalSort, GetAffected, GetDependencyChain, Visualize
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/graph/**"]

  - name: graph-test-coverage
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Check that the graph tests cover:
      1. Simple linear dependency chain (A -> B -> C)
      2. Diamond dependency (A -> B, A -> C, B -> D, C -> D)
      3. Cycle detection (A -> B -> C -> A)
      4. Self-dependency detection
      5. Unknown dependency detection
      6. Empty graph
      7. Single node with no dependencies
      8. TopologicalSort produces valid ordering (every node appears after its dependencies)
      9. GetAffected returns correct transitive dependents
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/graph/**"]

  - name: graph-tests-pass
    type: command_check
    command: cd src && uv run pytest graph/ -v
    exit_code: 0
---

# Graph Validations

The DAG is a critical correctness component. Cycle detection must never miss a cycle, and topological sort must always produce a valid build order. Tests must cover all edge cases.
